I just saw how it broke, not nice, but I still think we can improve this (I hope).

I am super radical with python and I don't even have user packages via pip installed I go for everything through a virtualenv, and I think this should be the case for jenkins too.
If you start from a clean install and you create/activate a virtualenv the path of the virtualenv becomes part of your path, so when maven installs tox it does not install it globally or even as part of the user site-packages, it resides just in the path of the virtualenv (e.g. in my case ~/.virtualenvs/beam/bin).
Maybe we can configure maven to behave more like this, because it is the most 'jailed' possible case.
